    <div class="well" id="the_l_in_linksys_wrt54gl_stand" >

        
        <a name="002144"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://wifinetnews.com/archives/006101.html">The L in Linksys WRT54GL Stands for Linux</a></h4>

        

        <p>Linksys are now explicitly catering to the hardware hacker market by keeping their excellent Linux-based WRT54G routers available at a premium after downgrading the &#8220;consumer&#8221; model.</p>

